command: npm run verify   (under a gate-faithful hermetic verify)
phase: 1 (0022 empirical-lognormal-default) — layer: hermetic verify (the gate sub-check that previously failed)

=== Why the prior implement (commit 165edeee) was rewound ===
Gate evidence (.backlog-logs/20260621_200627_0022_implement_p1.log.gate):

    > verify
    > npm run lint && npm run scan:forbidden && npm run scan:deps && npx secretlint "**/*" && vitest run
    > lint
    > eslint index.html --max-warnings 0
    sh: eslint: command not found     (=> exit 127)

Root cause (confirmed in lib/gate.sh:235-286, gate_hermetic_verify):
  - The gate materialises a FRESH detached worktree of the commit
    (`git worktree add --detach <tmp> HEAD`) and runs `verify_command` directly,
    N=green_reruns(3) times + 1 randomized-order pass, in ONE reused worktree.
  - It does NOT run `npm ci` / any dependency install. `node_modules/` is
    .gitignored, so a fresh worktree is BARE.
  - `net_disabled` is absent on this host => gate_net_wrap runs verify with the
    network available.
  - The old `verify_command` assumed deps were already installed, so its first
    layer (`eslint`) was not on PATH => `command not found` => exit 127.

=== Fix (production, non-test) ===
package.json `verify` now self-bootstraps deps from the lockfile when node_modules
is absent (same `command -v`/guard idiom already used by `scan:forbidden`):

  "verify": "{ [ -e node_modules/.bin/eslint ] || npm ci; } && npm run lint && \
             npm run scan:forbidden && npm run scan:deps && \
             npx secretlint \"**/*\" && vitest run"

No tool is changed/disabled/downgraded; the only addition is the documented
hermetic precondition (`npm ci`). In the working tree the guard finds eslint and
skips the install (fast); in the gate's bare worktree it runs `npm ci` once on
the first rerun, and reuses node_modules for the remaining reruns.

